# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#  HOW TO USE THIS FILE
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
#  1. This file (.env.example) is committed to git — it is safe to read and
#     share. It contains no real secrets.
#
#  2. Copy it to a NEW file called  .env.local  in the SAME folder as this file
#     (the project root, next to package.json):
#
#       cp .env.example .env.local
#
#     Then fill in your real values in .env.local.
#
#  3. .env.local is gitignored (.env.* pattern in .gitignore) — it will NEVER
#     be committed to git.
#
#  4. .env.local is ONLY needed on YOUR local machine when running:
#       pnpm upload-images    ← uploads photos to Cloudflare R2 (or Vercel Blob)
#
#     GitHub Actions and CI do NOT need any of these credentials.
#     The build reads the committed lib/generated/image-manifest.json — no uploads.
#
#  5. NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL is the one exception:
#     Set it as a GitHub Actions Variable (not a secret) so the build knows
#     the production URL for the sitemap and Open Graph tags.
#     GitHub repo → Settings → Variables → Actions → New repository variable
#
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════


# ── Site URL (optional — recommended for sitemap + OG tags) ──────────────────
# Set as a GitHub Actions Variable, not here.
# Also add to .env.local if you want it during local builds.
#
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL=https://your-domain.com


# ── Cloudflare R2 (recommended image storage) ─────────────────────────────────
# Required when: imageStorage.provider === "cloudflare-r2" in content/config.ts
# LOCAL ONLY — these values stay in .env.local on your machine.
#              Never put them in GitHub Actions secrets or Vercel env vars.
#
# How to get these values:
#   CF_R2_ACCOUNT_ID      — Cloudflare Dashboard → right sidebar → Account ID
#   CF_R2_ACCESS_KEY_ID   — Cloudflare Dashboard → R2 → Manage R2 API Tokens
#                           Create token: Object Read & Write, scoped to your bucket
#   CF_R2_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY — same token creation page
#   CF_R2_BUCKET          — the name of your R2 bucket
#   CF_R2_PUBLIC_URL      — public base URL for the bucket
#                           (your custom subdomain, e.g. https://images.your-domain.com,
#                            or the r2.dev URL Cloudflare assigns automatically)
#
# CF_R2_ACCOUNT_ID=
# CF_R2_ACCESS_KEY_ID=
# CF_R2_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=
# CF_R2_BUCKET=usedexchange-images
# CF_R2_PUBLIC_URL=https://images.your-domain.com


# ── Vercel Blob (alternative — for Vercel deployments) ───────────────────────
# Required when: imageStorage.provider === "vercel-blob" in content/config.ts
# Set in .env.local for local uploads AND in Vercel Dashboard env vars.
#
# How to get this token:
#   Vercel Dashboard → Storage → Blob → <your store> → Settings → Tokens
#
# BLOB_READ_WRITE_TOKEN=vercel_blob_rw_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
